President Trump visited the Otay Mesa Border Wall site in San Diego, California and gave remarks about the progress of the border wall construction. He expressed his excitement about the project and thanked the Army Corps of Engineers and the staff involved in the construction. The President explained that the wall is made of a combination of steel, concrete, and rebar, making it virtually impenetrable. He also highlighted the importance of having a wall that is see-through to allow visibility on both sides. The President mentioned that Mexico has been cooperating with the US and has deployed thousands of soldiers to help with border security. He discussed the progress of the construction, stating that the goal is to complete 400-500 miles of the wall by next year. The President also addressed other topics such as immigration policy, the situation in the Middle East, the Federal Reserve's interest rate cut, and the issue of homelessness in California.